% PsychToolbox:PsychTests.%% help PsychToolbox % For an overview, triple-click me & hit enter.%% These scripts exercise various aspects of the Psychophysics Toolbox, the% MATLAB environment, and your computer to document how well they work.% The results give insight into several performance issues, but may be too% cryptic for beginners. Start with ScreenTest or SpeedTest.% % help psychdemos % For demos, triple-click me and hit enter.% %   BackgroundingTest   - Test enhanced Backgrounding code in SCREEN.mex.%   BytesTest           - Test Bytes.mex.%   ClipTest            - Test copy and paste of matrices.%   ClutTest            - Test SCREEN 'SetClut' and 'GetClut' (color lookup table).%   ColorTest           - Test SCREEN functions that accept a "color" argument%   DriverTest          - Measures the screen's frame rate and synch with blanking.%   ExitTest            - Test automatic clean up on error.%   FitCumNormYNTest    - Fit a cumulative normal to yes-no data.%   FitWeibullTAFCTest  - Fit a Weibull to 2AFC data.%   FitWeibullYNTest    - Fit a Weibull to yes-no data.%   GammaTest           - Get and set SCREEN Gamma.%   GetClicksTest       - Test GetClicks/GetMouse event handling.%   GetImageTest        - Test SCREEN 'GetImage'.  This is also done in ScreenDemo.%   GetSecsTest         - Adjust rate of GetSecs to match Mac OS Time Manager.%   HelpTest            - Prints help text of every file in current directory.%   HideCursorTest      - Make sure cursor stays hidden while we wait for user input.%   LeakTest            - Test for memory leaks.%   LogTrapsTest        - Log system traps. WARNING: Requires MacsBug.%   LoopTest            - Measure variance of loop timing in MATLAB.%   MenuBarTest         - Checks for problems hiding the menu bar.%   MexTest             - Check PsychToolbox MEX files. Explain MATLAB Debugger.%   ModeTest            - Test SCREEN 'PutImage' modes.%   PixelSizeTest       - Does this crash your computer? Please tell us.%   PriorityTest        - Test timing at each priority level. %   PupilDiameterTest   - Test functions that compute pupil diameter from luminance.%   PutImageTest        - Test SCREEN 'PutImage' and 'GetImage'.%   QTPhotoTest         - Tests QT.mex with a photo.%   QTTest              - Tests QT.mex by making and showing a QuickTime movie.%   QuestTest           - Some Quest simulations, more elaborate than QuestDemo.%   ResolutionTest      - Use SCREEN Resolutions to print table of display resolutions.%   RushTest            - Test Rush's reduction of interruptions (variance).%   SaveAsEpsTest       - Checks out SCREEN SaveAsEps, which saves an image to disk.%   ScreenLeakTest      - Measures memory leakage associated with opening and closing windows.%   ScreenSaverTest     - Test effect of ScreenSaver.mex and SCREEN 'OpenWindow' on screen saver.%   ScreenTest          - Test showing of movies on all screens.%   SerialTest          - Exercise SERIAL.mex.%   SetClutTest         - Times SCREEN 'SetClut' at all pixelSizes and priorities.%   SndTest             - Compare quality of 8 and 16 bit sound.%   SpeedTest           - Time MATLAB's mean speed on various operations.%   TimeBlankingTest    - Synchronize computer to video frames.%   TimingTest          - Many ways to time an interval.%   TrolandTest         - Colorimetric conversions.%   WaitBlankingTest    - Test synchronization of computer and monitor.% Copyright (c) 1996-9 by David Brainard & Denis Pelli